# Tailwind CSS v4 Rules

## Setup
- Use `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin — no PostCSS config needed
- Entry CSS file: `@import "tailwindcss";`
- Design tokens via `@theme` block in the entry CSS file

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-primary: #3b82f6;
  --color-primary-dark: #2563eb;
  --color-secondary: #64748b;
  --color-success: #22c55e;
  --color-warning: #f59e0b;
  --color-error: #ef4444;
  --font-sans: "Inter", sans-serif;
  --radius-default: 0.5rem;
}
```

## Class Conventions
- Use utility classes directly in JSX — avoid `@apply` except in base styles
- Group classes logically: layout → spacing → sizing → typography → visual → states
- Use Tailwind's built-in responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`
- Use Tailwind's state prefixes: `hover:`, `focus:`, `disabled:`

```tsx
<button className="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white bg-primary rounded-default hover:bg-primary-dark focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary/50 disabled:opacity-50">
  Save
</button>
```

## Component Extraction
- When utility classes exceed ~6-8 classes, consider extracting a component (not a CSS class)
- Components are the right abstraction level — not CSS utility groups
- Use `clsx` or `tailwind-merge` for conditional classes

```tsx
import { clsx } from 'clsx';

type BadgeProps = { variant: 'success' | 'warning' | 'error'; children: React.ReactNode };

export function Badge({ variant, children }: BadgeProps) {
  return (
    <span className={clsx(
      'inline-flex items-center px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium rounded-full',
      variant === 'success' && 'bg-success/10 text-success',
      variant === 'warning' && 'bg-warning/10 text-warning',
      variant === 'error' && 'bg-error/10 text-error',
    )}>
      {children}
    </span>
  );
}
```

## Dark Mode
- Use `dark:` variant when implementing dark mode
- Define dark mode colors in `@theme` using CSS `light-dark()` or separate tokens
- Test both modes during development

## Don'ts
- Don't use `@apply` to create utility class groups (defeats Tailwind's purpose)
- Don't use inline `style` attributes for things Tailwind can handle
- Don't create custom CSS classes that duplicate Tailwind utilities
- Don't hardcode colors — always use theme tokens (`bg-primary`, not `bg-[#3b82f6]`)
